### Using `col()` in Range Checks

For range validations via [`Validate.col_vals_between()`](`Validate.col_vals_between`) and [`Validate.col_vals_outside()`](`Validate.col_vals_outside`) you
can use a mix of column references and fixed values:

::: {#73f3ebf7 .cell execution_count=13}
``` {.python .cell-code}
(
    pb.Validate(data=pb.load_dataset("small_table"))
    .col_vals_between(
        columns="d",
        left=pb.col("c"),
        right=10_000,
        na_pass=True
    )
    .interrogate()
)
